Once Jayden gave me her vision of a silhouetted image...I immediately understood the narrative. The silhouette is about subtle power. Jayden's beauty can be seen as a power...but when her looks are lost in shadow her power is still on display. Even in the absence of Jayden's iconic gaze you can still feel her intensity...it pierces through the shadow. There's a power in the way she stands. Even the angles her body makes, create solid and confident structures. 

For me, a silhouette represents strength because it is a bold and powerful image. When I see a silhouette, I am reminded of the strength and resilience that lies within each of us. The darkness that surrounds the figure represents the challenges and obstacles that we may face in life, but the silhouette itself stands strong and unwavering, a symbol of our ability to overcome those challenges and emerge even stronger on the other side. 

Photographer SHAMAYIM 
Model @jaydenrobison
